        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-28T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-28T11:00:00-05:00" n="839"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d839">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/596: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Oslo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-28T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 28, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 28—1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. The Norwegian Foreign Office today has handed me strictly confidential
                    memorandum protesting strongly against British plans for the seizure on high
                    seas of cargoes of German origin and [omission?] carried by neutral merchant
                    vessels stating that only small amounts of German goods are shipped by Norwegian
                    vessels, that such action would contravene rules of international law and that
                    Norway reserves the right to compensation for losses resulting therefrom. Text
                    by next pouch.<note n="60" xml:id="d839fn60">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
